🎙Pika World Breakfast Date - 3 August 2023🥁Equity markets were broadly lower on Tuesday after a downgrade of Fitch's US credit rating rating. While the move is nothing symbolic  it does reflect the ongoing focus on the sustainability of US debt. Notably  the 10-year Treasury yield is also climbing  supported by the expectation that the glut of Treasury bills will finally hit the market.We are also seeing the VIX climbing higher and breaking above the resistance level  and the upswing could further be a headwind for the equity market to trend higher. So  investors should prepare for some sizzling on the hot market as chill sprinkle the general sentiment.📪Firmer Labor Data🎯Moreover  the latest ADP Nonfarm payroll rose more sharply than expected  adding pressure to the Fed to possibly maintains its restrictive stance longer than expected  given a robust labour market.💼Employment data in focus🔦Investors will also look towards Friday's employment figure to understand the market condition.
